title: Advertisement for Dutch Settlement in Montana
creator: Great Northern Railway
description: Advertisement for the Chinook, Montana settlement in a Wisconsin-based Dutch language newspaper.
subject: newspaper advertisements;immigration;farmers (people in agriculture);farming (activity or system);newspapers
image_citation: Great Northern Railway. "Advertisement for Dutch Settlement in Montana." Delpher, Roosevelt Study Center, The Heyrman Pub. Co., De Pere, Brown, Wisconsin, October 5, 1910. https://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:331826631:mpeg21:a0001.
source: Delpher
image_alt_text: The image features a Dutch text titled "Naar Chinook! Naar Montana!" which translates to "To Chinook! To Montana!" It discusses the agricultural prospects in Montana, highlighting statements from Professor Shaw of the State Agricultural School in St. Paul, who recognizes Montana as a leading agricultural state. The text mentions Montana's achievements at the National Dry Farming Congress and emphasizes successful dry farming even during drought years. It encourages Dutch farmers to see the opportunities in Montana for themselves, noting the potential for high wheat yields around Chinook. The text aims to attract farmers to move to Montana, describing the region's benefits and available homesteads. Additionally, it provides travel details for those interested.

image_alt_text: A historical mural depicting a scene from the era of the Monroe Doctrine in 1823. Several men in 19th-century attire are gathered around a table with one man pointing at a globe. To the left, a military figure stands with a sword and another person stands beneath a palm tree. To the right, two men in traditional attire carry rifles. Below the mural reads, "THE MONROE DOCTRINE - 1823." Beneath the scene, text states: "WE MUST REMEMBER THAT ANY OPPRESSION ANY INJUSTICE ANY HATRED IS A WEDGE DESIGNED TO ATTACK OUR CIVILIZATION. FRANKLIN DELANO ROOSEVELT 1940." Decorative elements and classical motifs frame the images and text.

image_alt_text:
A collection of four artistic illustrations, each with its own theme:

1. A view of Cape Town with a map labeled "Cape Colony," featuring oil palm and diamond fields, and a coastal scene with sailboats.
2. A map labeled "British Guiana" with images of a pepper plantation and individuals involved in pepper harvesting, alongside a portrait of a person.
3. A map labeled "Argentine Republic" accompanied by scenes of a rider throwing a bola and a cityscape of Buenos Aires with sailing boats.
4. An illustration themed around Siam (Thailand), featuring an elephant with handlers, a map labeled "Siam," and a scene of boats in the "Floating City of Bangkok."
